  <summary>6/19/2001--Introduced.
Housing and Employment Opportunities Reform Act - Amends the Housing and Urban Development Act of 1968 to require that: (1) at least 30 percent of new employees hired by contractors performing services for assisted housing public or Indian housing agencies be low- or very low-income people; and (2) such agencies maintain a registry of eligible employees.</summary>
